page.title: 05Bicknoller Church
page.content: The Parish Church of St. George's has a number of interesting and unusual attractions. Once upon a time there was even a yew tree growing out of the top of the Church Tower. All round the outside walls of the Church there is an amazing collection of carvings. They show both angels and lots of vey frightening looking animals. Even inside there is a cariving of a man trying hard to escape from a large snake like creature. There are lots of lovely carvings on the end of many of the benches in Bicknoller Church. One really good carving shows St. George - this is because the Church is dedicated to St. George. Outside in the Churchyard there are some old stocks which looked really interesting.
